==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Eryngium
<hw>E*ryn"gi*um</hw> <pr>(⟦esl⟧*r⟦icr⟧n"j⟦icr⟧*⟦ucr⟧m)</pr>,
<pos>n.</pos> <ety>[NL., fr. Gr. <grk>'hry`ggion</grk>, dim. of
<grk>'h`ryggos</grk> eryngo; cf. L. <ets>eryngion</ets>,
<ets>erynge</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>A large genus of
umbelliferous plants somewhat like thistles in appearance, cosmopolitan
in distribution. <spn>Eryngium maritimum</spn>, or sea holly, has been
highly esteemed as an aphrodisiac, the roots being formerly
candied.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> genus <gen>Eryngium</gen>.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Eryngo</ent>⟦br⟧
